summary: Sansa Stark: Queen of the Gendrya Fanclub
body:
Sansa Stark: Queen of the Gendrya Fanclub

Her baby sister is in love even if she doesn’t know it yet and but she will and they’re perfect for each other. I mean he thinks its cute when Arya insults him that’s so adorable?!

Should be planning for winter but instead is planning their wedding and naming their future children.

Recruits Dadvos. Because you know he ships it too. He is the captain of this ship. He just wants all of his kids to be happy and plus he’s low key great at planning weddings so he and Sansa gossip about color schemes and plan for Lyanna Mormont to be the flower girl.

Come up with elaborate schemes to parent trap them but Arya always ends up ruining them because she’s a wild card™️

Starts dropping subtle hints. They go over Arya’s head. Starts dropping not so subtle hints. Nothing. Eventually gets so frustrated that she yells in the great hall “Gendry’s in love with you and you’re in love with him so just fucking kiss already!” Arya is in shock. Finally she speaks. “Sansa did you just say… fuck? Because that was so unladylike I’ve never been prouder to call you my sister!” Sansa then passes out because she can’t even.

When she wakes up she is absolutely furious because she missed Arya yanking Gendry down by the shirt and aggressively making out him in the great hall.

And now Jon knows more than he ever wanted to. He’s debating on whether or not to sic Ghost on Gendry or offer to walk Arya down the aisle. Actually he’s made up his mind because Waters, you bastard, watch your hand placEMENT.

And Bran’s just sitting there watching it all like I knew it.

title: PSA
body:
A much needed reminder to the GoT/ASOIAF community that adding tags which aren’t relevant to the content of your post is against the Tumblr Community Guidelines.

Tag your posts with the things they are actually about, so people can actually use these tags to find posts that are actually about these things. (Wild, I know. Who would have thought that that is what tags are for?)
